text: Central Java is a province in Indonesia. It is on the island of Java. ==People== The government reported that 35,557,249 people lived in Central Java Province in 2015. ===Ethnic groups=== Group Total (%) Javanese 97.86 Sundanese 1.40 Chinese-Indonesian 0.43 Batak 0.07 Madurese 0.04 Arab- Indonesian 0.04 Malays 0.03 Minangkabau 0.02 was up Dayak 0.01 Bugis 0.01 Banjar 0.01 Others 0.08 Source: 2010 Census ==References==
title: Central Java
